      • height

        public int height(BinaryTree.TreeNode<E> node)
        Height method specifying a tree Recursively find the maximum distance between the rootval and the trees. Termination happens when all nodes are traversed, indicated by the state of a null node or a node with left and right null nodes.
        Parameters:
        node - - tree node to start with

      • getNumberOfNonLeaves

        public int getNumberOfNonLeaves()
        Default nonleaves method

      • getNumberOfNonLeaves

        public int getNumberOfNonLeaves(BinaryTree.TreeNode<E> node)
        Call getNumberOfNonLeaves function specifying a starting node. Recursively count the non-leaves in the subtree starting at the specified node. Nodes with null left and right pointers do not count, as they are leaves, and terminate the recursion. left and right paths that are not nulls are followed.
        Parameters:
        node - - tree node to start with

      • getNumberOfLeaves

        public int getNumberOfLeaves()
        Default getNumberOfLeaves method

      • getNumberOfLeaves

        public int getNumberOfLeaves(BinaryTree.TreeNode<E> node)
        Call getNumberOfLeaves function specifying a starting node. Recursively find the leaves of the tree starting at the supplied node. Recursion terminates, and the count increases, when the left and right null pointers are null: indicating a leaf has been found.
        Parameters:
        node - - tree node to start with
